Walking lunges
Kettle swings
BACK TO BACK!

1 min rest between rounds.

The best feeling I get, is after these workouts.

node.text:
During my isolation it was tough not being able to gym, but had to find the motivation to get some type of sweat in so I came up with a few workouts, so here’s a good one! try this if you’re stuck in the house or if your gym isn’t open!

-30 sec jump rope
-30 sec in and out squat jumps
-30 sec RDL to squat
-30 sec lunge up jumps
-30 sec alt side plank twists

Wearing my own @get_tighterr sweat belt to make me feel tight and to sweat a little extra durning my HIIT workouts 😁 you can pre order yours with the link in my bio! 
Sizes S-XXL (true to size)
I’m wearing a medium

So excited to be teaming up with @get_tighterr and coming out with my own logo sweat belt!!!

If you see my stories often, you see me using this everyday pretty much during cardio workout or high intensity to help with the jiggle or just to help sweat a little extra. 

If you’d like to support and get yourself one they are now available to pre order!! If you order now or before April 25th you’ll be able with to save money 😁

https://www.tighterr.com/products/getfitwjessica-series-sweat-belt or link in bio! ❤️

node.text:
You guys I’m OBSESSED with this dessert..
Literally every night I make this and eat it after dinner.
Here’s my little tutorial on how I make it!
- 3 egg whites
- 1 scoop @iammotiv8 dessert protein
- 2 TBS coca powder
- 1/2 cup plain pumpkin.
- dash baking powder 
Mix all together and bake on parchment paper for 15-20 min on 350 degrees.
Brownie by it’s self is around d 200 cal and it’s a pretty big size!

If you try this recipe let me know!!
————-
If you want to try this protein use my code MOTIV8JESSICA for free shipping!
This is cookie dough protein, their blueberry is also amazingggg.

node.text:
Sometimes I wonder if I had all the loose skin on my body removed, would I be completely happy with the way I look?

I’d like to think that but I’d probably find something else to be insecure about 😅
It’s sad because I know a lot of it has to do with social media and the way we compare ourselves. Body dysmorphia is SOOO real and I can’t wait for the day I can look at myself and be completely happy with the way I see myself. We are all so much more than that number on the scale, our clothing size, loose skin, etc.. as long as your healthy or working on it, that’s all that matters. Stay beautiful!! 🤟🏽✨

node.text:
Went on my first “real” hike today and I’m in love!!! My body was confused but I enjoyed it so much, I so wish Florida had big hiking trails 😭

I love the views butttttt the Florida beaches will always feel like home.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jessica on August 18, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and people standing.

node.text:
What was your wake up call?

Mine was the feeling of just being tired. Age 19 and I barely had energy to do anything! I felt uncomfortable in my clothes, uncomfortable in my body and just didn’t have the confidence I wanted to have. To this day, I still know that feeling and that’s enough to keep me motivated every single day 🙏🏽💪🏽
•
•
Join us September 6th for our next dietbet!

I will be giving away 4 $50 Amazon gift cards to 4 members when we hit 200 players!! 

ONLY PICKING MEMBERS THAT ARE ALREADY IN THE GAME SO IF YOU JOIN, DONT FORGET TO COMMENT ON THE POST TO ENTER❤️

Bet yourself $35 that you can lose 4% of your body weight in 4 weeks and if you make your goal, split the pot with the other winners. (YOUR BODY WEIGHT x .04 = HOW MUCH YOU’LL NEED TO LOSE)

Why join?
-Meet new people who are on the same journey as you from ALL AROUND THE WORLD🌎
 -Share recipes/workouts
-Weightloss tips and accountability
-Get paid to lose weight!

Link in bio to join to join or dietbet.com/Jessica

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jessica on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
There used to be days I dreamed of wearing clothes like this, but didn’t because I wasn’t comfortable with the way I looked, or couldn’t even find clothes like this because the women’s plus didn’t carry the style I wanted.
I went from a size 24 in jeans to a size 8-10 and a size 3x shirt to a small-medium. I remember trying on a size 14 jeans and I CRIED because I was so happy to be out of the plus size👏🏽
I deff gotta say, buying new clothes was probably one of the most motivating things during my weight loss. Keep a goal outfit for yourself and let it motivate you!💪🏽

node.text:
Read this to yourself:

“I am talented and motivated, even when I get tired and frustrated i will be patient with myself. I am motivating and inspiring others with my strength and determination and I am so proud of the person I have become!”

There is absolutely NO reason to speak negative to yourself. Make your thoughts and words kind because you are your biggest supporter 🤟🏽

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jessica on August 13, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and people standing.

node.text:
2 years ago today, I was going in for surgery to get the last biopsy of my cancerous lymph node.

2 years ago, I got told I was cancer free after 6 months of chemo, many scans, a month of radiation and almost a whole year of playing the waiting game.

Today I am 2 years CANCER FREE and I couldn’t be anymore thankful, I am so truly blessed to be where I am at in life. Thank you to Jesus and all his glory for giving me many many miracles and keeping me strong through my crazy life💕🤟🏽🙏🏽

Posted this on my story today, this video came up in my camera roll at the perfect time. Sometimes i can forget how hard I’ve worked to be where i am today. 

It’s a process. There will be days when you feel like giving up, but don’t. There will be days when you feel like you don’t have what it takes, but you do! There will be days when you feel like things aren’t going anywhere, but it is. Just know if you keep going you will be so glad you didn’t give up!

20 lb slam ball circuit and some deadlifts 💥

16 steps
15 slams
15 squat press
4x

Deadlift 10x4
Also went a little heavier and did some max pulls!!

Just try and push your hardest. You got it!!

Outfit from @ptulaactive 😍
Large bra
Med leggings
💗💗💗💗

—————-
Click the link in my bio for my 4 week at home program! 

This program is designed for anyone looking for guidance on getting a good workout in without a gym.

If you have dumbbells and resistance bands you’re all set! 💪🏽

-4 weeks consisting of 
•abs everyday
•HIIT warm up
•2 upper body days
•2 lower body days
•1 full body day
•recovery stretches 

Each exercise in the program is performed so you understand how to do it. 

Getfitwjessica.com or link in bio 🤗
